BigqueryClusterConfig.description: dbt-core allows either of the variants for the `cluster_by` to allow cluster on a single column or on multiple columns

PartitionConfig.description: dbt-core allows either of the variants for the `partition_by` in the model config but the bigquery-adapter throws RunTime error the behaviors are tested from the latest dbt-core + bigquery-adapter as this is written we're conformant to this behavior via here and via the `validate` method

time_ingestion_partitioning.description: When this is true, the [`BigqueryPartitionConfig::field`] will be used as the `_PARTITIONTIME` pseudo column _PARTITIONTIME: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/partitioned-tables#ingestion_time https://docs.getdbt.com/reference/resource-configs/bigquery-configs#partitioning-by-an-ingestion-date-or-timestamp
